{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A control used to edit properties of an object."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"EditorInspector","symbolKind":"class","roleHeading":"Class","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot15EditorInspectorC","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"EditorInspector","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EditorInspector","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EditorInspector"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the control that implements property editing in the editor’s Settings dialogs, the Inspector dock, etc. To get the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","type":"reference"},{"text":" used in the editor’s Inspector dock, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInterface\/getInspector()","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" will show properties in the same order as the array returned by "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Object\/getPropertyList()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a property’s name is path-like (i.e. if it contains forward slashes), "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" will create nested sections for “directories” along the path. For example, if a property is named "},{"code":"highlighting\/gdscript\/node_path_color","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", it will be shown as “Node Path Color” inside the “GDScript” section nested inside the “Highlighting” section."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a property has "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PropertyUsageFlags\/propertyUsageGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" usage, it will group subsequent properties whose name starts with the property’s hint string. The group ends when a property does not start with that hint string or when a new group starts. An empty group name effectively ends the current group. "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","isActive":true},{"text":" will create a top-level section for each group. For example, if a property with group usage is named ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Collide With"},{"text":" and its hint string is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"collide_with_"},{"type":"text","text":", a subsequent "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"collide_with_area"},{"type":"text","text":" property will be shown as “Area” inside the “Collide With” section. There is also a special case: when the hint string contains the name of a property, that property is grouped too. This is mainly to help grouping properties like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"font"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"font_color","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"font_size","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (using the hint string "},{"code":"font_","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a property has "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PropertyUsageFlags\/propertyUsageSubgroup"},{"type":"text","text":" usage, a subgroup will be created in the same way as a group, and a second-level section will be created for each subgroup."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unlike sections created from path-like property names, ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector"},{"text":" won’t capitalize the name for sections created from groups. So properties with group usage usually use capitalized names instead of snake_cased names.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This object emits the following signals:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertySelected","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyKeyed"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyDeleted","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/resourceSelected","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/objectIdSelected","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyEdited","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyToggled","isActive":true}]}]},{"conten